  "texts": [
    "Inductive biases are modeling assumptions (e.g.",
    "locality or recurrence) that are needed to make deep learning work 103, but often cause unwanted side-effects.",
    "For instance most DNNs have a spectral biasthey prefer low-resolution features and omit high-frequency information 104.",
    "This can lead to shortcut learning 105: e.g.",
    "an image classification DNN may pick up non-causal features, such as using a green background to predict a cow, hence failing if a cow is in front of a blue background."
